*  @IMOD:  REMINDER OF INTEGER DIVIDED BY INTEGER FOR IBM SYSTEM/36     *
*                                                                       *
*           LEFT OPERAND  IN AC0                                        *
*           XR2 POINTS TO FIRST BYTE OF RIGHT                           *
*           REMINDER IN AC0+7                                           *
*                                                                       *
*************************************************************************
*
*  METHOD:   USE @IDIV WHICH RETURNS REMINDER IN AC0+5
*
@IMOD    START
*
         EXTRN @AC0
         EXTRN @IDIV
*
ARR      EQU   8
PC       EQU   X'10'
ACC      EQU   @AC0+7           (RIGHTMOST BYTE OF AC0)
ACC_HI   EQU   @AC0+5           (RIGHTMOST BYTE OF UPPER 16 BITS IN AC0)
*
         ST    RETADDR,ARR
         B     @IDIV
         MVC   ACC(2),ACC_HI    REMINDER INSTEAD OF QUOTIENT TO ACC
         L     RETADDR,PC       RETURN!
*
RETADDR  DS    XL2
         END
